class="post_content"><p>Our &#8216;Save as PDF&#8217; service lets your visitors save your web pages as PDF without leaving your website. You control the settings for conversion and we will convert any page on your website that you choose. You get to choose from a lot of different settings to optimize your conversion and make sure the PDF looks exactly the way YOU want it.</p><p>All you need to do is put a link like below on your web site and if your visitors clicks on it we&#8217;ll do the rest!</p><pre class="brush: xml; light: true; title: ; notranslate" title="">&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.htm2pdf.co.uk/display&quot;&gt;Save this page as PDF&lt;/a&gt;</pre><p>In our members area you&#8217;ll be able to set all the defaults you need to control the conversion process like page format, margins, header &amp; footer etc.</p><p>We also allow you to override some of these defaults in the link on your web page. In order to do that you can append the following parameters to your link:</p><table
class="table table-bordered"><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>url</td><td>URL of the web page that you&#8217;d like have converted &#8211; this must be a URL on the same (sub-)domain and include the whole domain including the &#8216;http://&#8217;<br
/> Note: if you want to pass extra parameters to the URL you have to escape the ampersand (&amp;) sign in the URL to %26 (<a
href="http://www.htm2pdf.co.uk/converting-a-url-with-additional-parameters/">more info in our blog</a>)</td></tr><tr><td>filename</td><td>Filename for the PDF</td></tr><tr><td>pagesize</td><td>Set page size like A3, A4, Letter etc. Please refer to the <a
href="/page-sizing">list of allowed page sizes</a></td></tr><tr><td>orientation</td><td>Specify <em>portrait</em> or <em>landscape</em> orientation</td></tr><tr><td>width</td><td>Custom width of the PDF</td></tr><tr><td>height</td><td>Custom height of the PDF, if you specify the width, but not the height, then we fit the whole page into a one page PDF by auto-adjusting the height of the PDF.</td></tr><tr><td>left</td><td>Left margin</td></tr><tr><td>right</td><td>Right margin</td></tr><tr><td>top</td><td>Top margin</td></tr><tr><td>bottom</td><td>Bottom margin</td></tr><tr><td>unit</td><td>Unit for size &amp; margin settings. Can be &#8216;mm&#8217; (millimeters), &#8216;in&#8217; (inches) or &#8216;pt&#8217; (points). We&#8217;ll use mm in case you don&#8217;t specify a unit.</td></tr><tr><td>cmt <span
class="label label-important">New!</span></td><td>Set the CSS media type so you can influence better how your content is converted to PDF. We currently support the values <em>print</em> and <em>screen</em>. If you don&#8217;t specify one, we take the one you&#8217;ve set in the members area. The default there is <em>screen</em>.<br
/> <a
href="http://www.w3schools.com/css/css_mediatypes.asp">See w3schools</a> for more information on CSS media types.</td></tr><tr><td>links <span
class="label label-important">New!</span></td><td>Enable links in the PDF with the value <em>on</em> or disable links with the value <em>off</em>. The default is to enable links.</td></tr></tbody></table><p><small>Note on measurements: in case you only specify a height then we&#8217;ll ignore it; In case you only specify a width we&#8217;ll assume you want a single page PDF. In case you specify one or more margins, but not all, we&#8217;ll assume the others to be 0.</small></p><p><strong>Examples</strong><br
/> Below are some examples that show you how you can use this link in real life. Give them a try &#8211; they work and show the power of this service!</p><table
class="table table-bordered"><thead><tr><th>Description</th><th>HTML code</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><pre class="brush: plain; light: true; title: ; notranslate" title="">Get a single page PDF</pre></td><td><pre class="brush: xml; light: true; title: ; notranslate" title="">&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.htm2pdf.co.uk/display?width=300&quot;&gt;Save as PDF&lt;/a&gt;</pre></td></tr><tr><td><pre class="brush: plain; light: true; title: ; notranslate" title="">Get a different page as PDF</pre></td><td><pre class="brush: xml; light: true; title: ; notranslate" title="">&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.htm2pdf.co.uk/display?url=http://htm2pdf.co.uk/faq&quot;&gt;Save as PDF&lt;/a&gt;</pre></td></tr><tr><td><pre class="brush: plain; light: true; title: ; notranslate" title="">Save with a specific filename</pre></td><td><pre class="brush: xml; light: true; title: ; notranslate" title="">&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.htm2pdf.co.uk/display?filename=saveaspdf.pdf&quot;&gt;Save as PDF&lt;/a&gt;</pre></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Bonus function</strong><br
